post_text:
Get Your Sign in Time for the First Home Varsity Football Game!

Show your Raider Pride and become a member of the Raiders Rise Club! This new annual spirit campaign is sure to become a Sunnyvale tradition. Show off your school pride with a yard sign and a car decal.

Funds raised in the Raiders Rise campaign are not subject to state recapture and can go DIRECTLY to support the students and teachers of Sunnyvale.

Help your school win the campus competition! The campus with the most #RAIDERSRISE memberships wins a special prize from Mr.Williams!

Raiders Rise Club Membership: $100/Year
Includes a Raiders Rise yard sign and vehicle decal

Stop by the Sunnyvale Schools Administration Building to purchase your membership from Emily White, Director of Communications and Marketing.

post_text:
Raider family,

We continue to review the new guidance from Attorney General Paxton's office and the ongoing discussion from state officials regarding the Return to School for all Texas schools. The SISD administrative team is currently exploring these options. One of the first steps in this process is to consult our Board of Trustees in a called meeting on Monday, August 3, 2020. We appreciate your patience as we continue to work through this ever-changing situation.

In the meantime, if you have questions, please feel free to e-mail them to info@sunnyvaleisd.com.

Our goal is for our students to return to school in the safest manner. We will keep you updated with information as soon as possible.

Thank you again for your support.
SISD Administration

post_text:
2020 Seniors! As the first SHS graduating class to hold its commencement in Raider Stadium, you are MAKING HISTORY!

Commemorate this incredible moment (and all your days at Sunnyvale ISD) by purchasing a personalized brick that will be included in the SISD Legacy Walk. The Legacy Walk is just at the entrance of Raider Stadium- right where you graduate!

What a great way to celebrate the Class of 2020! Imagine if every member of the class purchased a brick!

Proceeds benefit the Gwinn Blankenship Scholarship Fund - which benefits graduating seniors each spring.

The Legacy Walk is located near the entrance of Raider Stadium. Let's help it become a huge success!!

Anyone - any grade, any age - can order a Legacy Walk brick! All Raiders and community members are welcome!

www.bricksrus.com/donorsite/SunnyvaleRaiders

May 3 at 4:19 PM ¬∑

**Adopt‚Ä¢A‚Ä¢Senior**

Sunnyvale Moms, thank you for your patience as SHS manages the best way to assure each senior receives recognition. After some discussion, it has been decided that SHS will head up the Adopt A Senior program for our 2020 Seniors. However, we cannot make this successful without your help and donations. An account has been set up at the SISD Administration building, 417 E Tripp Road, and we would welcome any donations, in the form of cash or check. If you have an item you would like to donate to our 140 Seniors, please feel free to contact me at Raquel.banno@sunnyvaleisd.com. We will begin the distributions on May 8 and continuing on, each Friday, through the end of May. We hope you will help SHS make every senior‚Äôs dream come true! I look forward to working with you all.

Mrs. Raquel Banno

#RaidersRise #sunnyvalelovestheirseniors

The Brown Bag Teacher
March 26 at 9:24 PM ¬∑

Using Google Meet but want to see the faces of all your students? Easy fix! Download the ‚ÄúGoogle Met Grid Extension‚Äù. Then, when you create a Meet, the grey grid/window below will be added to your video screen permenatly. Select it during a meet and there you go. Easy peasy!

Why you might use Meet vs Zoom?
-Zoom is hackable and not as secure.
-Meet allows for any length of meeting and up to 250 people in attendance.
-If your school/district uses Google Suite, it embedded seamlessly.
-With ANY new resource (Google Meet or Zoom), you need to check with your tech department about information the website or resource collects to ensure FERPA rights aren‚Äôt violated!

For students in current grades 7-12.

Dear parents,

Your student is invited to join us on a once-in-a-lifetime international travel experience with their peers during summer of 2021 to Italy & Greece!!

Please come to hear all the details including the destination, itinerary, and cost of this trip as well as the official opening of enrollment!

This meeting will be held on Thursday February 13th at 6:30PM in the Sunnyvale High School Auditorium. There are limited spots on this tour but we would love to have you attend this meeting to learn more about this exciting opportunity!

shared_text:
Sharing Life Community Outreach
January 30 at 11:00 AM ¬∑

Souper Bowl of Caring is happening now through February 3rd. Here are a list of ways you can get involved:
1. Have your church take up a special offering by passing around soup bowls, pots, & pans.
2. Take up money and food donations at your book club, small group, sporting events, and Sunday school class.
3. Have everyone at your Super Bowl watch party bring a donation.
4. Make this a competition with your class at school. Giving can be super fun!
Together WE can tackle hunger!!! Every dollar adds up and fights hunger!
#SharingLifeTX
#TackleHunger
*Thank you to Sunnyvale ISD and Kearney's Feed Yard for having collection bins! If you bring a donation, Kearney's will give you free chips & queso. Yum!
Sunnyvale Independent School District
Kearney's Feed Yard
